On June 24, the U.S. Supreme Court overturned the Roe vs. Wade ruling, deciding that there is no longer a federal constitutional right to an abortion. In today's American society, "anti-democratic" characteristics of its political system are becoming more and more obvious. From gun control to abortion rights, is the U.S. making great strides toward a constitutional crisis? Is this a dangerous signal for the Democratic Party, the 2022 mid-term elections and the 2024 presidential election?